reviews_data.review_text: Great and expensive but worth it

Worst Whole Foods i have seen in the USA.  Constant "refrigeration" issues prevents this location from providing fresh seafood, or meats. The produce looks/is pathetic.  Not sure how Amazon evaluates different Whole Foods stores but they should shut this one down.
Great place for finding healthy and hood quality groceries. Very friendly and helpful staff.

Kiki was extremely pleasant as she walked us to customer service for a return. She went the extra mile and with a smile. The silver haired clerk, think her name is Emma/Elaine was also happy. Wanted management to know customer service is not dead. Had a crazy morning so their service brightened my day a little. Thanks
The store is clean, well stocked and the employees very helpful. The Amazon counter is wonderful and I’m so happy it’s in Whole Foods.
A great whole foods
Excellent Whole Foods with the right amount of options in a safe and clean environment.

In my 17 years of shopping at Whole Foods, I can confidently state that this location is a zero, whereby all others have been 10s. Consistently: empty shelves during peak hours; much of the produce is not fresh (yesterday the sole bunch of fresh mint available was so dry it was crispy). Worst of all, my last TWO visits were met with no fresh seafood or meat available as the cooling stations in the fish and meat depts were broken. Poor, poor management. Corporate: please address, once and for all, as this is UNACCEPTABLE! Having to funnel my business to Harris Teeter as I am left with no choice.
Great selection of vegan and vegetarian options. Carries unique gourmet foods you can't get elsewhere.
A typical Whole Foods. Good variety but mostly house brands.  Quick check out, especially with the pay via a palm reader.

On multiple visits (including today), it baffles me why there is so little food out, and few choices at the hot bar during peak hours (like lunch time). It comes out later (11:15-11:30 am)  and my guess less that half of the food bin options have something.   The sandwich bar looks closed indefinitely.  My wild guess is this is a staffing, lack of supervision leadership issue.  Unknown yet it's weird.
Amazing meat department
Love Whole Foods. Always clean and great customer service

Every time I buy berries in a pack here they are moldy already. I even open the pack to see, but unless I root through the berries in the store I can't tell that there's a layer of mold right under the surface. For the prices, the produce should really be fresh.

Edit: I tried again years later. Behold the moldy berries.
I like it

Whole Foods Market in SouthPark truly stands out as a premier grocery destination! From the moment you walk in, the store is impeccably clean and well-organized, making for a genuinely pleasant shopping experience.
One of the absolute highlights here is the incredible customer service. The staff consistently goes above and beyond, always friendly, helpful, and ready to assist with a smile. It really makes a difference when you feel genuinely welcomed and supported in your shopping.

And let's talk about the food! The ready-made options are a lifesaver for busy days. They're not just convenient, but genuinely delicious, offering a wide variety of fresh, high-quality meals that are perfect for a quick lunch or dinner. You can tell they put thought and care into their prepared foods.

But here's a pro tip: the pizza is a secret gem! Seriously, it's a surprising win. Freshly made with great ingredients, it's easily one of the best quick pizza options around and definitely worth trying.

Overall, Whole Foods Market SouthPark provides an exceptional shopping experience. It's clean, well-stocked, and the staff are fantastic. Highly recommend!
Never the same since amazon got involved. Sad to see they carry apeel on produce.
Waiting in line for Amazon return for 10min.  They need to hire more people. The line is huge right now and it’s during the week
Good and well organized store with fresh and high quality products
Basically, the same layout of a typical Whole Foods Market. It has a parking deck below.

Like the convenience of an Amazon drop off, but the woman behind the counter did not seem to like her job. To have the style/environment of what I would say is a bit more on the upscale side of grocery shopping, the experience with the people was not.

I was trying to order a pizza, however the gentleman in kitchen area told me to come back in 10 -15 mins. Once I did that I had to wait another15-20 for the gentleman to make the pizza. Disappointing experience.

The pickup service at the Fairview location is awesome 👍🏽!  Made my order, went to pick it up, checked in I was there from my phone, and shortly after I found a space they were handing me my order. Didn't even have to get out‼️😁
Parking:  They're always busy, so the parking is... Eh! Depending on the time you go, you may have to circle a few times to find a park,

Sorry but this Whole Foods has gone downhill. General Manager Ryan Flynn please take notice of this. The nuts for the fresh nut butter are always out. Many employees act like they can't possibly know where the products are or can't help you with it if they're doing something else. Today they told me they couldn't cut the fresh fish in smaller portions because the hot water was out. There is never any Good Culture yogurt. Always out.

Abbie is one exception at the Customer Service counter -was extremely nice and tried to help me but explained that this store is the last stop on the cottage cheese delivery route and this Whole Foods gets whatever is left. She said others complain about the poor stocking of this store consistently.

Respectfully ---Whole Foods can do better. Please do better. It's sad to me that the coffee bar was never reopened. I've been told so many times it cannot be staffed.

You're Whole Foods after all!! I hope you will step up your business practices.
The best place to shop in the Southpark area. Fast service!!! Loved it!
Nice Whole Foods. Good selection of produce and nice staff. Upstairs has a nice dining area with small play area for kids.

I like Whole Foods and especially on Tuesdays and Fridays, they have some good deals, but you can’t always get everything on your list here. Great bakery and deli! The integration between your Amazon app and Whole Foods makes check out a breeze!

This store might be a little higher in prices . But does offers a lot more in your shopping experience.  The hot bar for food is the best in the city . The wine section is just unbelievable and has a drinking area while your wife shops, you can have a glass of wine . The employees  are first class and well trained and eager  to help .. I just love coming here ..

I am extremely disappointed with my recent experience at [fairview rd Location in Charlotte ]. I dined there with my kids and was served uncooked chicken, which poses a serious health risk. When I brought this to the staff’s attention and requested to speak with a manager, I expected concern and immediate action. Instead, I was met with indifference and unprofessionalism.
Food safety should be a top priority for any establishment, especially one that prides itself on quality. The lack of concern from the management was unacceptable. This kind of negligence could lead to severe health consequences, especially for children.
Whole Foods, I urge you to take this issue seriously. Proper food preparation and customer safety should never be overlooked. I hope to see accountability and improvement so that no other family has to experience this.

Don't most stores stock overnight or closer to store closing time, and not 6:00 in the evening?   And this is not the first, or even the second time I have experienced this. For the love of god avoid getting any food from the hot bar or sushi, both are HORRIBLE. And ironically, not only is the food from the hot bar disgusting and dry, it’s m not even hot as the name suggests… HELLO?

I love Whole Foods and going to one is a rare treat for me. But this was the absolute worst WF I’ve ever been in. I was there at 6 PM on a Thursday. All I wanted was hot soup and a sandwich, or some hot prepared food as we are in a hotel with no microwave. The soup station and the little hot bar were empty. The coffee counter was closed for good? We weren’t sure.

The salad bar was a mess. Most of the food trays were reduced to some dry bits, or had obviously been sitting out, untended, for hours.. there was a big plop of hummus that was literally turning a crusty brown on top and the edges. The dressing bottles were covered in slopped over dressing. I picked up the vinaigrette and it almost slipped out of my hands. There weren’t any napkins, so I eventually wiped my hands on the counter just to get the grease off them. There was a small selection of hot things that looks like they were warmed over and put out - hours ago. Completely unappetizing.

I walked out with a cup of romaine lettuce, a couple of grapes and grape tomatoes, and some picked onions - but yeah, no dressing. That and a bottle of iced tea cost $8. I know it’s very expensive to eat there so I was fine paying a lot of money for tasty food. 100% disappointed.

After being loyal WFM customers since 2009, we've decided we will no longer give our business to Whole Foods.
- produce quality is just awful. Every single time we go shopping, we find produce just rotting on the shelves. And the pattern continues, with half of the purchase rotting in the fridge within a day or two. And no, it's not because it's organic, we buy a mix of conventional and organic.
- the hot bar - the sizzler has a better selection and quality. Selection is abysmal and on multiple occasions I've gotten food that is undercooked or spoiled (tasted and smelled sour). I'm not even mentioning the food that is dry and crusty bc it's been sitting out for hours.
- bakery items are subpar at best. Pastries are almost always undercooked, and why don't they slice bread for customers anymore?
- grocery shelves are half empty and items are out of stock for weeks.
- lastly, I'd like to comment on the poor workers, who are lifeless, clearly overwhelmed and overworked and sometimes rude and frustrated. Why does it take 20 minutes to get some cheese sliced at the deli? I don't blame them, I blame the management, because it is so evident that the managers are apathetic to workers needs.
Farewell WFM and congratulations to Amazon for ruining a good thing.

Though I enjoy the quality of the products sold by this establishment,  it seems to have grown so large at the expense of the personal and engaging experience I often looked forward to. I rarely visit now.

There is always something wrong at this Whole Foods and it’s beyond obnoxious.  Did you want a smoothie at lunch time? Nope, the smoothie bar is closed.  Did you want a sandwich? Nope, the sandwich bar is closed for whatever new reason and no employee knows when it’s coming back.  Cool, love the convenience of having a half-out of service Whole Foods near me.

My experience at the checkout is terrible more times than not.  Today an older gentleman in front of me did not had his prime card.  The clerk told him to walk to his car and get it.  He had maybe 10 items.  8 minutes later he comes back.   I told her I would gladly scan my card so he can have the prime specials. But no.  Holdup the line for 10 minutes while we wait so he can save a $1.00. He had 10 items for gods sake.  Geeze. This is the stupidity you deal with at the checkout.

Today a produce employee was stocking carrots.  I asked him if they were out of limes as there were none out   He looked at the empty shelf and said we are out. We don’t have any. He made no effort to look in the back.  5 minutes later he sees a box with limes.  Oh hey, here are some limes! You’re in luck.  OMG.

Here’s another annoying thing it seems  they will charge an item incorrectly charging you organic when it’s not.  especially lemons and avocados. It happened today on my lemon.  It had a scan sticker with the number but they charged me organic price.  I watch the price on the monitor while they scan my items or check my receipt before I head out.  They have no way of returning your money over the phone.  You have to remember to take your receipt back on your next visit.  How convenient for Whole Foods.

My experience with management is they are disinterested in your feedback. When I say something they look at me like I have a third eye.   I personally think it’s a management issue at the CLT store.

They need to talk with Harris Teeter as they truly get customer service.  Harris Teeter is working on their organic food section    When they do I will never step foot back into Whole Foods.  Their employees lack of enthusiasm and good customer service is maddening to me.  They can do better.  Frankly, Whole Foods is too expensive.

They're not just convenient, but genuinely delicious, offering a wide variety of fresh, high-quality meals that are perfect for a quick lunch or dinner. But here's a pro tip: the pizza is a secret gem! Seriously, it's a surprising win. Freshly made with great ingredients, it's easily one of the best quick pizza options around and definitely worth trying.

Overall, Whole Foods Market SouthPark provides an exceptional shopping experience. It's clean, well-stocked, and the staff are fantastic. Highly recommend!

After being loyal WFM customers since 2009, we've decided we will no longer give our business to Whole Foods.
- produce quality is just awful. Every single time we go shopping, we find produce just rotting on the shelves. And the pattern continues, with half of the purchase rotting in the fridge within a day or two. And no, it's not because it's organic, we buy a mix of conventional and organic.
- the hot bar - the sizzler has a better selection and quality. Selection is abysmal and on multiple occasions I've gotten food that is undercooked or spoiled (tasted and smelled sour). I'm not even mentioning the food that is dry and crusty bc it's been sitting out for hours.
- bakery items are subpar at best. Pastries are almost always undercooked, and why don't they slice bread for customers anymore?
- grocery shelves are half empty and items are out of stock for weeks.
- lastly, I'd like to comment on the poor workers, who are lifeless, clearly overwhelmed and overworked and sometimes rude and frustrated. Why does it take 20 minutes to get some cheese sliced at the deli? I don't blame them, I blame the management, because it is so evident that the managers are apathetic to workers needs.
Farewell WFM and congratulations to Amazon for ruining a good thing.
